Initiation schools are set to resume in December after being suspended due to COVID-19. AFP/Alexander Joe JOHANNESBURG - Initiation schools will resume in December. The Congress of Traditional Leaders of South Africa has given go-ahead. READ:Â Contralesa warns of repercussions if initiation schools stay closed The schools were barred from operating due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The traditional practice is usually held in winter and summer. Contralesa in Gauteng says all schools should follow COVID-19 safety and health protocols.